{
  "texts": [
    "India alone appears to have a significantly large number of single authored papers; others are Morocco and Iran which also seem to lean more into individual work.",
    "Nevertheless, these three countries have fewer co-authored papers, so, there is actually not much collaboration between them.",
    "The smaller yellow areas in the figure imply that there is limited MCPs but they are substantially rare than the other type of international collaborations.",
    "The inset line chart gives similar information as the line chart with the total number of articles, SCPs, and MCPs reducing from year 2000 to year 2007.",
    "This trend shows that although some countries publish a lot of papers there is still a space for one to enhance their level of collaboration on the international level."
  ]
}